Certainly! To rephrase "The dog jumped the fence" while clearly conveying its meaning, you could say: "The dog leaped over the fence."

Here's how you could format this rephrased sentence using LaTeX:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}

The dog leaped over the fence.

\end{document}
```

This LaTeX code will produce a simple document with the rephrased sentence.
